# Architecture Overview

## Runtime modes

- `api` mode
    - starts Gin HTTP server
    - starts baseline refresh worker
    - starts incident tracking worker
- `manage` mode
    - starts Bubble Tea TUI for service and probe config management
- `seed` mode
    - inserts fake services and user reports for development

## Main layers

- `api/`
    - route handlers and server wiring
    - returns HTML fragments for HTMX and JSON when `Accept: application/json`
- `storage/`
    - the data access layer
    - all SQL and cache access should live here
    - handlers and workers should call storage methods, not write ad hoc SQL
- `algorithm/`
    - status decision logic and thresholds
    - single source of truth for service status classification
- `workers/`
    - background loops that maintain derived state
    - hourly baseline refresh
    - minutely incident open/close reconciliation
- `services/`
    - infrastructure setup helpers for Postgres and Redis
- `structs/`
    - GORM schema and config structs
- `templates/`
    - full pages plus HTMX components

## Data stores

- Postgres is source of truth for services, reports, baselines, probes, incidents
- Redis is used as short TTL cache for expensive list reads

## Important architecture rules

- keep status logic in `algorithm.DetermineStatus`
- keep report window usage consistent with `algorithm.ReportWindow`
- keep list endpoints batched to avoid N+1 lookups
- treat probe data as optional so the app works before probe runner exists
